SUMMARY:Rice World Cup Cities Hack
DESCRIPTION:The Rice World Cup Cities Hack is a sustainability-focused virtual data hackathon tied to the FIFA World Cup 2026. Teams will work with real-world urban datasets to build data management and visualization solutions\, analyzing the sustainability impact of the World Cup on host cities like Houston. \n📅 Kick-Off Workshop: June 23-24 at The Ion\, Houston – Register – https://forms.gle/uBfedtqia27Zmafe7\n💻 Virtual Hackathon: June 23-September 15\n🏆 $10\,000 Grand Prize | $17\,500 in total prizes \nChallenge tracks include Transportation & Access\, Energy-Food-Water Nexus\, Public Health & the Built Environment\, and High-Intensity Corridors & Future Growth Districts. Interdisciplinary teams are encouraged! \n\n\nRegister for Hack by June 22: https://rice-urban-sustainability.devpost.com/
URL:https://iondistrict.com/event/rice-world-cup-cities-hack/
LOCATION:Ion\, 4201 Main Street\, Houston\, TX\, 77002\, United States
CATEGORIES:Founders & Startups,General Community,Networking,Start Here
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://iondistrict.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/RiceHackathonFlyer-1.pdf.png
END:VEVENT
